# Create a new branch for a feature or refactoring\ngit checkout -b feature/new-feature\n\n# Work on the feature or refactoring\n# ...\n\n# Commit changes\ngit add .\ngit commit -m "Implement new feature"\n\n# Pull latest changes from trunk and resolve conflicts if any\ngit checkout trunk\ngit pull origin trunk\ngit checkout feature/new-feature\ngit merge trunk\n\n# After resolving conflicts and testing, merge back to trunk\ngit checkout trunk\ngit merge feature/new-feature\n\n# Push changes to the remote repository\ngit push origin trunk